parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air bag sensor/control module can cause the air bags to deploy unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. Additionally, it can also cause the air bags to fail to deploy in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The air bag light illuminates on the dashboard
the vehicle shuts down or loses power
smoke or fire residue is visible
and there is an ammonia or burnt plastic smell.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air bags to deploy in the event of a crash can increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The air bags fail to deploy in a crash
the vehicle is involved in a low-impact frontal collision
and the side impact air bags deploy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadvertent deployment of the air bags can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The air bags deploy without warning
and there is smoke or fire residue visible.

The malfunction of the horn can cause inconvenience and potentially lead to safety issues if the driver is unable to alert other road users.
symptoms: Horn suddenly goes off and won't stop
